imdb.plot outline: The Skegness Natureland seal sanctuary is well known for rescuing and rehabilitating orphaned and injured seal pups that become stranded on Lincolnshire beaches. Visitors can see the seals at various stages of their rehabilitation and hear about the rescue work at feeding times. We follow the staff and seal keepers as they treat, feed and finally release two seals back into their natural habitat.
